            "questionText": "<p>A developer is writing a web application that is deployed on Amazon EC2 instances behind an internet-facing Application Load Balancer (ALB). The developer must add an Amazon CloudFront distribution in front of the ALB. The developer also must ensure that customer data from outside the VPC is encrypted in transit.<br><br>Which combination of CloudFront configuration settings should the developer use to meet these requirements? (Choose two.)</p>",
            "explanation": "<p>üìù <u>T√≥m t·∫Øt ƒë·ªÅ:</u></p><ul><li><p>Web application tr√™n <strong>EC2 instances</strong> behind <strong>internet-facing ALB</strong></p></li><li><p>Developer ph·∫£i th√™m <strong>CloudFront distribution</strong> ph√≠a tr∆∞·ªõc ALB</p></li><li><p>Y√™u c·∫ßu: ƒë·∫£m b·∫£o <strong>customer data from outside VPC</strong> ƒë∆∞·ª£c <strong>encrypted in transit</strong></p></li><li><p>Ch·ªçn <strong>2 ƒë√°p √°n</strong></p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚úÖ <u>ƒê√°p √°n ƒë√∫ng:</u></p><p><strong>Set the Origin Protocol Policy setting to Match Viewer.</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Origin Protocol Policy = Match Viewer</strong> ƒë·∫£m b·∫£o connection t·ª´ CloudFront ƒë·∫øn ALB (origin) d√πng same protocol nh∆∞ viewer request</p></li><li><p>N·∫øu viewer d√πng HTTPS, CloudFront s·∫Ω d√πng HTTPS ƒë·∫øn origin</p></li><li><p>Encrypt data <strong>between CloudFront and ALB</strong> (inside AWS network nh∆∞ng outside VPC)</p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Set the Viewer Protocol Policy setting to Redirect HTTP to HTTPS.</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Viewer Protocol Policy = Redirect HTTP to HTTPS</strong> force t·∫•t c·∫£ viewers ph·∫£i d√πng HTTPS</p></li><li><p>ƒê·∫£m b·∫£o connection <strong>between users and CloudFront</strong> ƒë∆∞·ª£c encrypted</p></li><li><p>Automatically redirect HTTP requests sang HTTPS</p></li></ul><p><strong>K·∫øt h·ª£p 2 settings</strong> ‚Üí encrypted in transit cho c·∫£ 2 ƒë∆∞·ªùng: viewer-to-CloudFront v√† CloudFront-to-origin</p><p></p><p><u>C√°c ƒë√°p √°n sai:</u></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Restrict viewer access by using signed URLs.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Signed URLs d√πng cho <strong>access control/authorization</strong>, kh√¥ng li√™n quan ƒë·∫øn encryption in transit</p></li><li><p>Kh√¥ng gi·∫£i quy·∫øt y√™u c·∫ßu encrypt data</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Enable field-level encryption.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Field-level encryption ch·ªâ encrypt <strong>specific sensitive fields</strong> trong POST requests</p></li><li><p>Kh√¥ng encrypt to√†n b·ªô data in transit</p></li><li><p>Qu√° specific cho use case n√†y</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Enable automatic object compression.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Object compression gi√∫p <strong>reduce bandwidth v√† improve performance</strong></p></li><li><p>Kh√¥ng li√™n quan ƒë·∫øn encryption in transit</p></li></ul><p></p><p>üîë <u>Tips and tricks:</u></p><ul><li><p><strong>\"Encryption in transit\"</strong> ‚Üí focus v√†o <strong>protocol policies</strong> (HTTP vs HTTPS)</p></li><li><p><strong>CloudFront encryption c√≥ 2 legs</strong>:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Viewer ‚Üí CloudFront</strong> = Viewer Protocol Policy</p></li><li><p><strong>CloudFront ‚Üí Origin</strong> = Origin Protocol Policy</p></li></ul></li><li><p><strong>Redirect HTTP to HTTPS</strong> = force encryption cho viewers</p></li><li><p><strong>Match Viewer</strong> = maintain same protocol t·ª´ viewer ƒë·∫øn origin</p></li><li><p><strong>Signed URLs</strong> = authorization, kh√¥ng ph·∫£i encryption</p></li></ul><p></p><p>üìñ <u>Reference:</u></p><ul><li><p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonCloudFront/latest/DeveloperGuide/using-https-cloudfront-to-custom-origin.html\">Require HTTPS for communication between CloudFront and your custom origin</a></p></li></ul>",
