            "questionText": "<p>A company has an internal website that contains sensitive data. The company wants to make the website public. The company must ensure that only employees who authenticate through the company's OpenID Connect (OIDC) identity provider (IdP) can access the website. A developer needs to implement authentication without editing the website.<br><br>Which combination of steps will meet these requirements? (Choose two.)</p>",
            "explanation": "<p>üìù <u>T√≥m t·∫Øt ƒë·ªÅ:</u></p><ul><li><p>Company c√≥ <strong>internal website</strong> ch·ª©a <strong>sensitive data</strong>, mu·ªën make <strong>public</strong></p></li><li><p>Ch·ªâ <strong>employees authenticate qua company's OIDC IdP</strong> m·ªõi ƒë∆∞·ª£c access</p></li><li><p>Developer c·∫ßn implement authentication <strong>without editing the website</strong></p></li><li><p>H·ªèi: combination of steps n√†o ƒë√°p ·ª©ng y√™u c·∫ßu? (Ch·ªçn <strong>2 ƒë√°p √°n</strong>)</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚úÖ <u>ƒê√°p √°n ƒë√∫ng:</u></p><p><strong>Create a public Application Load Balancer.</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>ALB</strong> h·ªó tr·ª£ <strong>built-in authentication</strong> v·ªõi OIDC IdP</p></li><li><p>C√≥ th·ªÉ authenticate users <strong>tr∆∞·ªõc khi forward traffic</strong> ƒë·∫øn backend</p></li><li><p><strong>Kh√¥ng c·∫ßn modify website code</strong> - authentication ƒë∆∞·ª£c handle ·ªü load balancer layer</p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Configure a listener for the load balancer that listens on HTTPS port 443. Add a default authenticate action providing the OIDC IdP configuration.</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>HTTPS port 443</strong> ƒë·∫£m b·∫£o <strong>secure connection</strong> cho sensitive data</p></li><li><p><strong>Authenticate action</strong> v·ªõi OIDC IdP configuration integrate tr·ª±c ti·∫øp v·ªõi company IdP</p></li><li><p><strong>Default action</strong> apply authentication cho t·∫•t c·∫£ requests</p></li><li><p>ALB t·ª± ƒë·ªông redirect users ƒë·∫øn OIDC IdP ƒë·ªÉ authenticate</p></li></ul><p></p><p><u>C√°c ƒë√°p √°n sai:</u></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Create a public Network Load Balancer.</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>NLB</strong> ho·∫°t ƒë·ªông ·ªü <strong>Layer 4</strong> (TCP/UDP), kh√¥ng h·ªó tr·ª£ application-layer features nh∆∞ authentication</p></li><li><p>NLB kh√¥ng c√≥ built-in OIDC authentication capability</p></li><li><p>Ch·ªâ ALB (Layer 7) m·ªõi support authentication</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Configure a listener for the load balancer that listens on HTTP port 80. Add a default authenticate action providing the OIDC IdP configuration.</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>HTTP port 80</strong> kh√¥ng encrypted, kh√¥ng ph√π h·ª£p cho <strong>sensitive data</strong></p></li><li><p>Authentication credentials s·∫Ω b·ªã expose qua plaintext</p></li><li><p>Ph·∫£i d√πng <strong>HTTPS port 443</strong> cho secure communication</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Configure a listener for the load balancer that listens on HTTPS port 443. Add a default AWS Lambda action providing an Amazon Resource Name (ARN) to a Lambda authentication function.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Require <strong>custom Lambda function</strong> ƒë·ªÉ implement authentication logic</p></li><li><p>Ph·ª©c t·∫°p h∆°n v√† require code development</p></li><li><p>ALB ƒë√£ c√≥ <strong>native OIDC authentication</strong>, kh√¥ng c·∫ßn Lambda</p></li></ul><p></p><p>üîë <u>Tips and tricks:</u></p><ul><li><p><strong>\"Authentication without editing website\"</strong> ‚Üí <strong>ALB built-in authentication</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>\"OIDC IdP\"</strong> ‚Üí ALB h·ªó tr·ª£ native OIDC integration</p></li><li><p><strong>\"Sensitive data\"</strong> ‚Üí ph·∫£i d√πng <strong>HTTPS (port 443)</strong>, kh√¥ng d√πng HTTP</p></li><li><p><strong>ALB vs NLB</strong>:</p><ul><li><p><strong>ALB (Layer 7)</strong> = support authentication, routing rules</p></li><li><p><strong>NLB (Layer 4)</strong> = TCP/UDP only, no authentication</p></li></ul></li><li><p><strong>ALB authenticate action</strong> = no code changes needed</p></li></ul><p></p><p>üìñ <u>Reference:</u></p><ul><li><p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/elasticloadbalancing/latest/application/listener-authenticate-users.html#configure-user-authentication\">Authenticate users using an Application Load Balancer - Configure user authentication</a></p></li></ul>",
