            "questionText": "<p>A company wants to migrate applications from its on-premises servers to AWS. As a first step, the company is modifying and migrating a non-critical application to a single Amazon EC2 instance. The application will store information in an Amazon S3 bucket. The company needs to follow security best practices when deploying the application on AWS.<br><br>Which approach should the company take to allow the application to interact with Amazon S3?</p>",
            "explanation": "<p>üìù <u>T√≥m t·∫Øt ƒë·ªÅ:</u></p><ul><li><p>Company migrate application t·ª´ <strong>on-premises</strong> l√™n <strong>single EC2 instance</strong></p></li><li><p>Application c·∫ßn <strong>store information in S3 bucket</strong></p></li><li><p>Ph·∫£i follow <strong>security best practices</strong></p></li><li><p>C√°ch approach n√†o ƒë·ªÉ allow application interact with S3?</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚úÖ <u>ƒê√°p √°n ƒë√∫ng:</u></p><p><strong>Create an IAM role that has the necessary access to Amazon S3. Attach the role to the EC2 instance.</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>IAM role</strong> l√† <strong>best practice</strong> cho EC2 ƒë·ªÉ access AWS services</p></li><li><p><strong>Temporary credentials</strong> t·ª± ƒë·ªông rotate, kh√¥ng c·∫ßn manage access keys</p></li><li><p><strong>Principle of least privilege</strong> - ch·ªâ grant necessary S3 permissions</p></li><li><p><strong>Kh√¥ng l∆∞u credentials</strong> trong code ho·∫∑c EC2 instance</p></li><li><p><strong>Secure</strong> - credentials kh√¥ng bao gi·ªù exposed ho·∫∑c hardcoded</p></li></ul><p></p><p><em>Architecture:</em></p><p><span class=\"node-imageComponent\"><span class=\"image-component\"><img class=\"resizable-image\" src=\"https://static.cloudexam.pro/courses/3/1759324516920-7q1k6htv-image.png\" alt=\"\" title=\"\" width=\"775\" height=\"293.9752604166667\" style=\"max-width: 775px\" data-keep-ratio=\"true\"></span></span></p><p></p><p><u>C√°c ƒë√°p √°n sai:</u></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Create an IAM role that has administrative access to AWS. Attach the role to the EC2 instance.</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Administrative access</strong> vi ph·∫°m <strong>principle of least privilege</strong></p></li><li><p>Grant qu√° nhi·ªÅu permissions kh√¥ng c·∫ßn thi·∫øt</p></li><li><p>Security risk n·∫øu EC2 b·ªã compromise</p></li><li><p>Ch·ªâ c·∫ßn S3 access, kh√¥ng c·∫ßn admin access</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Create an IAM user. Attach the AdministratorAccess policy. Copy the generated access key and secret key. Within the application code, use the access key and secret key along with the AWS SDK to communicate with Amazon S3.</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>IAM user v·ªõi access keys</strong> kh√¥ng ph·∫£i best practice cho EC2</p></li><li><p><strong>Hardcoded credentials</strong> trong code l√† security risk</p></li><li><p><strong>AdministratorAccess</strong> vi ph·∫°m least privilege</p></li><li><p>Access keys c√≥ th·ªÉ b·ªã leaked, kh√¥ng t·ª± ƒë·ªông rotate</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Create an IAM user. Attach a policy that provides the necessary access to Amazon S3. Copy the generated access key and secret key. Within the application code, use the access key and secret key along with the AWS SDK to communicate with Amazon S3.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Tuy c√≥ ƒë√∫ng permissions (S3 only), nh∆∞ng v·∫´n d√πng <strong>hardcoded access keys</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>IAM user</strong> kh√¥ng ph·∫£i best practice cho EC2 instances</p></li><li><p>Access keys ph·∫£i manage manually v√† c√≥ th·ªÉ b·ªã expose</p></li><li><p>IAM role t·ªët h∆°n v√¨ t·ª± ƒë·ªông rotate credentials</p></li></ul><p></p><p>üîë Tips and tricks:</p><ul><li><p><strong>\"EC2 access AWS services\"</strong> ‚Üí <strong>IAM role</strong>, kh√¥ng d√πng IAM user</p></li><li><p><strong>\"Security best practices\"</strong> ‚Üí lo·∫°i options c√≥:</p><ul><li><p>Hardcoded access keys</p></li><li><p>Administrative/excessive permissions</p></li></ul></li><li><p><strong>IAM role vs IAM user cho EC2</strong>:</p><ul><li><p><strong>IAM role</strong> = temporary credentials, auto-rotate, best practice</p></li><li><p><strong>IAM user</strong> = long-term credentials, manual management, security risk</p></li></ul></li><li><p><strong>\"Necessary access\"</strong> = principle of least privilege, ch·ªâ grant S3 permissions c·∫ßn thi·∫øt</p></li></ul><p></p><p>üìñ <u>Reference:</u></p><ul><li><p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/iam-roles-for-amazon-ec2.html\">IAM roles for Amazon EC2</a></p></li></ul>",
