            "attemptAnswerId": 329547,
            "questionId": 5339,
            "questionText": "<p>A company is building a serverless application. The application uses an API key to authenticate with a third-party application. The company wants to store the external API key as a part of an AWS Lambda configuration. The company needs to have full control over the AWS Key Management Service (AWS KMS) keys that will encrypt the API key and should be visible only to authorized entities.<br><br>Which solution will meet these requirements?</p>",
            "explanation": "<p>üìù <u>T√≥m t·∫Øt ƒë·ªÅ:</u></p><ul><li><p>Company build <strong>serverless application</strong> d√πng <strong>API key</strong> ƒë·ªÉ authenticate v·ªõi third-party application</p></li><li><p>Mu·ªën store <strong>external API key</strong> trong <strong>Lambda configuration</strong></p></li><li><p>Y√™u c·∫ßu:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Full control over KMS keys</strong> ƒë·ªÉ encrypt API key</p></li><li><p><strong>Ch·ªâ c√°c entities ƒë∆∞·ª£c ph√¢n quy·ªÅn</strong> m·ªõi th·∫•y ƒë∆∞·ª£c API key</p></li></ul></li><li><p>Solution n√†o ƒë√°p ·ª©ng y√™u c·∫ßu?</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚úÖ <u>ƒê√°p √°n ƒë√∫ng:</u></p><p><strong>Store the API key in AWS Lambda environment variables. Create an AWS KMS customer managed key to encrypt the API key.</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Lambda environment variables</strong> l√† part of Lambda configuration (ƒë√°p ·ª©ng y√™u c·∫ßu \"store as part of Lambda config\")</p></li><li><p><strong>Customer managed KMS key</strong> cho ph√©p <strong>full control</strong> over key (rotation, policies, access)</p></li><li><p>C√≥ th·ªÉ restrict ai c√≥ quy·ªÅn decrypt b·∫±ng KMS key policy</p></li><li><p>API key <strong>visible only to authorized entities</strong> th√¥ng qua KMS key permissions</p></li></ul><p><u>C√°c ƒë√°p √°n sai:</u></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Store the API key in AWS Systems Manager Parameter Store as a string parameter. Use the default AWS KMS key that AWS provides to encrypt the API key.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Parameter Store kh√¥ng ph·∫£i <strong>part of Lambda configuration</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Default AWS KMS key</strong> kh√¥ng cho <strong>full control</strong> (AWS managed, kh√¥ng customize ƒë∆∞·ª£c)</p></li><li><p>Kh√¥ng ƒë√°p ·ª©ng y√™u c·∫ßu \"full control over KMS keys\"</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Store the API key in the code repository. Use an AWS managed key to encrypt the code repository.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Store credentials trong <strong>code repository</strong> vi ph·∫°m security best practices</p></li><li><p><strong>AWS managed key</strong> kh√¥ng cho full control</p></li><li><p>API key c√≥ th·ªÉ b·ªã expose trong version control history</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Store the API key as an Amazon DynamoDB table record. Use an AWS managed key to encrypt the API key.</strong></p><ul><li><p>DynamoDB kh√¥ng ph·∫£i <strong>part of Lambda configuration</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>AWS managed key</strong> kh√¥ng cho full control</p></li><li><p>Th√™m complexity kh√¥ng c·∫ßn thi·∫øt</p></li></ul><p></p><p>üîë <u>Tips and tricks:</u></p><ul><li><p><strong>\"Full control over KMS keys\"</strong> ‚Üí <strong>Customer managed key</strong> (kh√¥ng ph·∫£i AWS managed key)</p></li><li><p><strong>\"Part of Lambda configuration\"</strong> ‚Üí <strong>Lambda environment variables</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>KMS key types</strong>:</p><ul><li><p><strong>AWS managed key</strong> = AWS qu·∫£n l√Ω, no full control</p></li><li><p><strong>Customer managed key</strong> = full control (policies, rotation, access)</p></li></ul></li><li><p><strong>\"Visible only to authorized entities\"</strong> ‚Üí KMS key policy control access</p></li><li><p><strong>Parameter Store/DynamoDB</strong> = external storage, kh√¥ng ph·∫£i \"Lambda configuration\"</p></li></ul><p></p><p>üìñ <u>Reference:</u></p><ul><li><p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/lambda/latest/dg/configuration-envvars-encryption.html\">Securing Lambda environment variables</a></p></li></ul><p></p><p>KMS Key Policy - Ch·ªâ cho ph√©p authorized entities decrypt API key</p><pre><code>{\n  \"Version\": \"2012-10-17\",\n  \"Statement\": [\n    {\n      \"Sid\": \"Enable IAM User Permissions\",\n      \"Effect\": \"Allow\",\n      \"Principal\": {\n        \"AWS\": \"arn:aws:iam::123456789012:root\"\n      },\n      \"Action\": \"kms:*\",\n      \"Resource\": \"*\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"Sid\": \"Allow Lambda execution role to decrypt\",\n      \"Effect\": \"Allow\",\n      \"Principal\": {\n        \"AWS\": \"arn:aws:iam::123456789012:role/MyLambdaExecutionRole\"\n      },\n      \"Action\": [\n        \"kms:Decrypt\",\n        \"kms:DescribeKey\"\n      ],\n      \"Resource\": \"*\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"Sid\": \"Allow specific developers to decrypt\",\n      \"Effect\": \"Allow\",\n      \"Principal\": {\n        \"AWS\": [\n          \"arn:aws:iam::123456789012:user/developer1\",\n          \"arn:aws:iam::123456789012:user/developer2\"\n        ]\n      },\n      \"Action\": [\n        \"kms:Decrypt\",\n        \"kms:DescribeKey\"\n      ],\n      \"Resource\": \"*\"\n    }\n  ]\n}</code></pre><p></p><p><strong>Gi·∫£i th√≠ch:</strong></p><p>‚úÖ <strong>Authorized entities (ƒë∆∞·ª£c ph√©p decrypt):</strong></p><ul><li><p>Lambda execution role (ƒë·ªÉ Lambda function decrypt API key)</p></li><li><p>Developer1 v√† Developer2 (specific users ƒë∆∞·ª£c authorize)</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Unauthorized entities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>B·∫•t k·ª≥ IAM user/role n√†o kh√¥ng n·∫±m trong policy ‚Üí <strong>kh√¥ng th·ªÉ decrypt</strong></p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>K·∫øt qu·∫£:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Ch·ªâ Lambda function v√† 2 developers ƒë∆∞·ª£c ch·ªâ ƒë·ªãnh m·ªõi xem ƒë∆∞·ª£c API key</p></li><li><p>T·∫•t c·∫£ entities kh√°c b·ªã deny</p></li></ul>",
