            "questionId": 5343,
            "questionText": "<p>A company uses an AWS Lambda function to call a third-party service. The third-party service has a limit of requests each minute. If the number of requests exceeds the limit, the third-party service returns rate-limiting errors.<br><br>A developer needs to configure the Lambda function to avoid receiving rate limiting errors from the third-party service.<br><br>Which solution will meet these requirements?</p>",
            "explanation": "<p>üìù <u>T√≥m t·∫Øt ƒë·ªÅ:</u></p><ul><li><p>Lambda function call <strong>third-party service</strong></p></li><li><p>Third-party service c√≥ <strong>limit of requests each minute</strong></p></li><li><p>N·∫øu exceed limit ‚Üí third-party service returns <strong>rate-limiting errors</strong></p></li><li><p>Developer c·∫ßn configure Lambda ƒë·ªÉ <strong>tr√°nh rate limiting errors</strong></p></li><li><p>H·ªèi: solution n√†o ƒë√°p ·ª©ng y√™u c·∫ßu?</p></li></ul><p>‚úÖ <u>ƒê√°p √°n ƒë√∫ng:</u></p><p><strong>Set the reserved concurrency on the Lambda function to match the number of concurrent requests that the third-party service allows.</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Reserved concurrency</strong> limit s·ªë <strong>concurrent executions</strong> c·ªßa Lambda function</p></li><li><p><strong>Throttle requests</strong> ·ªü Lambda level tr∆∞·ªõc khi g·ªçi third-party service</p></li><li><p><strong>Prevent exceeding</strong> third-party service rate limit</p></li><li><p>V√≠ d·ª•: n·∫øu third-party cho ph√©p 10 requests/minute ‚Üí set reserved concurrency = 10</p></li></ul><p><u>C√°c ƒë√°p √°n sai:</u></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Decrease the memory that is allocated to the Lambda function.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Memory allocation kh√¥ng li√™n quan ƒë·∫øn rate limiting</p></li><li><p>Ch·ªâ ·∫£nh h∆∞·ªüng performance v√† cost</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Set the provisioned concurrency on the Lambda function to match the number of concurrent requests that the third-party service allows.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Provisioned concurrency d√πng ƒë·ªÉ <strong>reduce cold start</strong>, kh√¥ng limit concurrent executions</p></li><li><p>Kh√¥ng prevent Lambda t·ª´ vi·ªác exceed third-party rate limit</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Increase the timeout value that is specified on the Lambda function.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Timeout ch·ªâ tƒÉng th·ªùi gian Lambda ƒë∆∞·ª£c ch·∫°y</p></li><li><p>Kh√¥ng gi·∫£m s·ªë requests g·ª≠i ƒë·∫øn third-party service</p></li></ul><p></p><p>üîë <u>Tips and tricks:</u></p><ul><li><p><strong>\"Rate limiting\" + \"limit concurrent requests\"</strong> ‚Üí <strong>Reserved concurrency</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Reserved concurrency</strong> = limit max concurrent executions (throttle)</p></li><li><p><strong>Provisioned concurrency</strong> = pre-warmed instances (reduce cold start)</p></li><li><p><strong>Memory/Timeout</strong> = performance tuning, kh√¥ng li√™n quan rate limiting</p></li></ul><p>üìñ <u>Reference:</u></p><ul><li><p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/lambda/latest/dg/configuration-concurrency.html\">Configuring reserved concurrency for a function</a></p></li></ul>",
            "correctAnswer": [
                "<p>Set the reserved concurrency on the Lambda function to match the number of concurrent requests that the third-party service allows.</p>"
            ],
            "selectedAnswers": null,
            "isCorrect": null,
            "isFlagged": false,
            "answers": [
                "<p>Set the reserved concurrency on the Lambda function to match the number of concurrent requests that the third-party service allows.</p>",
                "<p>Decrease the memory that is allocated to the Lambda function.</p>",
                "<p>Set the provisioned concurrency on the Lambda function to match the number of concurrent requests that the third-party service allows.</p>",
                "<p>Increase the timeout value that is specified on the Lambda function.</p>"
            ],
            "answersPos": "[0,1,2,3]",
            "pos": 20
