            "questionText": "<p>A developer has an application that asynchronously invokes an AWS Lambda function. The developer wants to store messages that resulted in failed invocations of the Lambda function so that the application can retry the call later.<br><br>What should the developer do to accomplish this goal with the LEAST operational overhead?</p>",
            "explanation": "<p>üìù <u>T√≥m t·∫Øt ƒë·ªÅ:</u></p><ul><li><p>Developer c√≥ application <strong>asynchronously invokes Lambda function</strong></p></li><li><p>Mu·ªën <strong>store messages that resulted in failed invocations</strong></p></li><li><p>Application c√≥ th·ªÉ <strong>retry call sau</strong></p></li><li><p>Solution n√†o v·ªõi <strong>LEAST operational overhead</strong>?</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚úÖ <u>ƒê√°p √°n ƒë√∫ng:</u></p><p><strong>Implement a dead-letter queue for discarded messages. Set the dead-letter queue as an event source for the Lambda function.</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Dead-letter queue (DLQ)</strong> l√† native feature c·ªßa Lambda cho async invocations</p></li><li><p><strong>Automatic capture</strong> failed messages without custom code</p></li><li><p><strong>Set DLQ as event source</strong> ‚Üí Lambda automatically retry messages t·ª´ DLQ</p></li><li><p><strong>LEAST overhead</strong> - minimal configuration, no custom logic needed</p></li></ul><p></p><p><u>C√°c ƒë√°p √°n sai:</u></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Set up Amazon CloudWatch Logs log groups to filter and store the messages in an Amazon S3 bucket. Import the messages in Lambda. Run the Lambda function again.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Require nhi·ªÅu manual steps: filter logs, export to S3, import, retry</p></li><li><p>High operational overhead v·ªõi custom implementation</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Configure Amazon EventBridge to send the messages to Amazon Simple Notification Service (Amazon SNS) to initiate the Lambda function again.</strong></p><ul><li><p>EventBridge kh√¥ng t·ª± ƒë·ªông capture failed Lambda invocations</p></li><li><p>Th√™m complexity v·ªõi SNS integration kh√¥ng c·∫ßn thi·∫øt</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Send Amazon EventBridge events to an Amazon Simple Queue Service (Amazon SQS) queue. Configure the Lambda function to pull messages from the SQS queue. Run the Lambda function again.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Require thay ƒë·ªïi invocation pattern t·ª´ async sang SQS polling</p></li><li><p>Th√™m operational overhead v·ªõi SQS management</p></li></ul><p></p><p>üîë <u>Tips and tricks:</u></p><ul><li><p><strong>\"Async Lambda failures\" + \"retry\"</strong> ‚Üí <strong>Dead-letter queue (DLQ)</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>DLQ options</strong>: SQS queue ho·∫∑c SNS topic</p></li><li><p><strong>DLQ as event source</strong> = automatic retry mechanism</p></li><li><p><strong>LEAST overhead</strong> ‚Üí d√πng native Lambda features (DLQ)</p></li></ul><p></p><p>üìñ <u>Reference:</u></p><ul><li><p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/lambda/latest/dg/invocation-async-retain-records.html#invocation-dlq\">Adding a dead-letter queue</a></p></li></ul><h3><strong>Adding a dead-letter queue:</strong></h3><p>Nh∆∞ m·ªôt <strong>alternative</strong> cho on-failure destination, b·∫°n c√≥ th·ªÉ configure function v·ªõi <strong>dead-letter queue</strong> ƒë·ªÉ save discarded events cho further processing.</p><p><strong>Dead-letter queue ho·∫°t ƒë·ªông gi·ªëng on-failure destination:</strong></p><ul><li><p>ƒê∆∞·ª£c d√πng khi event fails t·∫•t c·∫£ processing attempts ho·∫∑c expires m√† kh√¥ng ƒë∆∞·ª£c processed</p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Kh√°c bi·ªát:</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>DLQ:</strong> ch·ªâ c√≥ th·ªÉ add/remove ·ªü <strong>function level</strong> (kh√¥ng ph·∫£i version/alias level)</p></li><li><p><strong>On-failure destinations:</strong> support nhi·ªÅu target types h∆°n v√† include details v·ªÅ function's response</p></li></ul><hr><p></p><p><strong>Reprocess events t·ª´ DLQ:</strong></p><p>C√≥ 2 c√°ch:</p><ol><li><p>Set DLQ as event source cho Lambda function ‚Üí Lambda t·ª± ƒë·ªông retry</p></li><li><p>Manually retrieve events t·ª´ DLQ</p></li></ol><hr><p></p><p><strong>L·ª±a ch·ªçn DLQ type:</strong></p><p><strong>Amazon SQS queue (Standard):</strong></p><ul><li><p>Queue holds failed events cho ƒë·∫øn khi retrieved</p></li><li><p>Choose SQS n·∫øu expect <strong>single entity</strong> (1 Lambda function ho·∫∑c CloudWatch alarm) x·ª≠ l√Ω failed event</p></li></ul><p><strong>Amazon SNS topic (Standard):</strong></p><ul><li><p>Topic relays failed events ƒë·∫øn <strong>multiple destinations</strong></p></li><li><p>Choose SNS n·∫øu expect <strong>multiple entities</strong> x·ª≠ l√Ω failed event</p></li><li><p>V√≠ d·ª•: send ƒë·∫øn email + Lambda function + HTTP endpoint</p></li></ul><p>‚ö†Ô∏è <strong>FIFO queues v√† SNS FIFO topics KH√îNG ƒë∆∞·ª£c supported</strong></p><hr><p></p><p><strong>Permissions required:</strong></p><p>Function's execution role c·∫ßn permissions ƒë·ªÉ:</p><ul><li><p>Send events ƒë·∫øn queue/topic</p></li><li><p>N·∫øu target encrypted b·∫±ng customer managed KMS key ‚Üí c·∫ßn KMS permissions</p></li></ul>",
