            "questionText": "<p>A company recently deployed a new serverless user portal. Users have reported that part of the portal is slow. The initial analysis found a single Amazon API Gateway endpoint that is responsible for the performance issues. The endpoint integrates with an AWS Lambda function. However, the Lambda function interacts with other APIs and AWS services.<br><br>How can a developer find the source of the increased response time by using operational best practices?</p>",
            "explanation": "<p>üìù <u>T√≥m t·∫Øt ƒë·ªÅ:</u></p><ul><li><p>Company deploy <strong>serverless user portal</strong>, users report <strong>portal is slow</strong></p></li><li><p>Analysis t√¨m th·∫•y <strong>single API Gateway endpoint</strong> g√¢y performance issues</p></li><li><p>Endpoint integrates v·ªõi <strong>Lambda function</strong></p></li><li><p>Lambda function <strong>interacts v·ªõi other APIs v√† AWS services</strong></p></li><li><p>H·ªèi: l√†m th·∫ø n√†o ƒë·ªÉ <strong>x√°c ƒë·ªãnh nguy√™n nh√¢n l√†m tƒÉng response time</strong> theo <strong>best practices v·ªÅ operations</strong>?</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚úÖ <u>ƒê√°p √°n ƒë√∫ng:</u></p><p><strong>Instrument the Lambda function with the AWS X-Ray SDK. Add HTTP and HTTPS interceptors and SDK client handlers. Deploy the updated Lambda function. Turn on X-Ray tracing. After accumulating enough usage data, use the X-Ray service map to examine the average response times to determine the likely sources.</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>X-Ray</strong> ƒë∆∞·ª£c thi·∫øt k·∫ø ƒë·∫∑c bi·ªát cho <strong>distributed tracing</strong> v√† <strong>performance analysis</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Service map</strong> visualize to√†n b·ªô request flow v√† <strong>response times c·ªßa t·ª´ng service</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Interceptors v√† SDK handlers</strong> t·ª± ƒë·ªông trace external API calls v√† AWS service calls</p></li><li><p><strong>Operational best practice</strong> cho troubleshooting distributed applications</p></li></ul><p></p><p><em>V√≠ d·ª• Service map</em></p><p><span class=\"node-imageComponent\"><span class=\"image-component\"><img class=\"resizable-image\" src=\"https://static.cloudexam.pro/courses/3/1760081087662-avye1lxu-image.png\" alt=\"\" title=\"\" width=\"720\" height=\"484.5375\" style=\"max-width: 720px\" data-keep-ratio=\"true\"></span></span></p><p></p><p><u>C√°c ƒë√°p √°n sai:</u></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Update the Lambda function by adding logging statements with high-precision timestamps before and after each external request. Deploy the updated Lambda function. After accumulating enough usage data, examine the Amazon CloudWatch logs for the Lambda function to determine the likely sources for the increased response time.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Manual logging kh√¥ng ph·∫£i best practice, require nhi·ªÅu code changes</p></li><li><p>Kh√≥ ph√¢n t√≠ch v√† li√™n k·∫øt d·ªØ li·ªáu t·ª´ nhi·ªÅu services</p></li><li><p>Kh√¥ng c√≥ visualization nh∆∞ X-Ray service map</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Review the Lambda function's Amazon CloudWatch metrics by using the metrics explorer. Apply anomaly detection to the Duration metric and the Throttles metric. Review the anomalies to determine the likely sources.</strong></p><ul><li><p>CloudWatch metrics ch·ªâ show <strong>overall Lambda performance</strong>, kh√¥ng break down theo external calls</p></li><li><p>Kh√¥ng identify ƒë∆∞·ª£c <strong>which specific API/service</strong> g√¢y bottleneck</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Use Amazon CloudWatch Synthetics to create a new canary. Turn on AWS X-Ray tracing on the canary. Configure the canary to scan the user portal. After accumulating enough usage data, use the CloudWatch Synthetics canary dashboard to view the metrics from the canary.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Synthetics canary d√πng cho <strong>monitoring availability</strong>, kh√¥ng ph·∫£i troubleshooting existing performance issues</p></li><li><p>Kh√¥ng trace internal Lambda function calls</p></li></ul><p></p><p>üîë <u>Tips and tricks:</u></p><ul><li><p><strong>\"Find source of latency\" + \"distributed system\"</strong> ‚Üí <strong>AWS X-Ray</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>X-Ray service map</strong> = visualize request flow v√† response times</p></li><li><p><strong>Operational best practice</strong> = X-Ray tracing, kh√¥ng ph·∫£i manual logging</p></li><li><p><strong>CloudWatch metrics</strong> = overall metrics, <strong>X-Ray</strong> = detailed tracing</p></li></ul><p></p><p>üìñ <u>Reference:</u></p><ul><li><p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/lambda/latest/dg/services-xray.html\">Visualize Lambda function invocations using AWS X-Ray</a></p></li></ul>",
