            "questionText": "<p>A company uses Amazon Simple Queue Service (Amazon SQS) to decouple its microservices architecture. Some messages in an SQS queue contain sensitive information. A developer must implement a solution that encrypts all the data at rest.<br><br>Which solution will meet this requirement?</p>",
            "explanation": "<p>üìù <u>T√≥m t·∫Øt ƒë·ªÅ:</u></p><ul><li><p>Company d√πng <strong>SQS</strong> ƒë·ªÉ decouple microservices architecture</p></li><li><p>Some messages trong SQS queue ch·ª©a <strong>sensitive information</strong></p></li><li><p>Developer ph·∫£i implement solution <strong>encrypts all data at rest</strong></p></li><li><p>Solution n√†o ƒë√°p ·ª©ng y√™u c·∫ßu?</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚úÖ <u>ƒê√°p √°n ƒë√∫ng:</u></p><p><strong>Enable server-side encryption for the SQS queue by using an SQS managed encryption key (SSE-SQS).</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>SSE-SQS</strong> encrypt <strong>data at rest</strong> automatically</p></li><li><p>SQS managed key kh√¥ng c·∫ßn qu·∫£n l√Ω key rotation</p></li><li><p>ƒê√°p ·ª©ng ƒë√∫ng requirement \"encrypt all data at rest\"</p></li></ul><p></p><p><u>C√°c ƒë√°p √°n sai:</u></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Use the aws:SecureTransport condition in the queue policy to ensure that only HTTPS (TLS) is used for all requests to the SQS queue.</strong></p><ul><li><p>HTTPS/TLS encrypt <strong>data in transit</strong>, kh√¥ng ph·∫£i <strong>data at rest</strong></p></li><li><p>Kh√¥ng ƒë√°p ·ª©ng y√™u c·∫ßu encrypt at rest</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Use AWS Certificate Manager (ACM) to generate an SSL/TLS certificate. Reference the certificate when messages are sent to the queue.</strong></p><ul><li><p>ACM certificates d√πng cho <strong>encryption in transit</strong>, kh√¥ng ph·∫£i at rest</p></li><li><p>SQS kh√¥ng require custom SSL certificates</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Set a message attribute in the SQS SendMessage request for messages that are sent to the queue. Set the Name to ENCRYPT. Set the Value to TRUE.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Message attributes kh√¥ng t·ª± ƒë·ªông encrypt data</p></li><li><p>ƒê√¢y kh√¥ng ph·∫£i valid encryption method</p></li></ul><p></p><p>üîë <u>Tips and tricks:</u></p><ul><li><p><strong>\"Encrypt data at rest\"</strong> ‚Üí <strong>Server-side encryption (SSE)</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>\"Encrypt data in transit\"</strong> ‚Üí <strong>HTTPS/TLS</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>SQS encryption options</strong>:</p><ul><li><p>SSE-SQS (SQS managed key)</p></li><li><p>SSE-KMS (customer managed key)</p></li></ul></li><li><p><strong>ACM certificates</strong> = in transit, kh√¥ng ph·∫£i at rest</p></li></ul><p></p><p>üìñ <u>Reference:</u></p><ul><li><p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSSimpleQueueService/latest/SQSDeveloperGuide/sqs-server-side-encryption.html\">Encryption at rest in Amazon SQS</a></p></li></ul>",
