            "questionText": "<p>A developer is storing many objects in a single Amazon S3 bucket. The developer needs to optimize the S3 bucket for high request rates.<br><br>How should the developer store the objects to meet this requirement?</p>",
            "explanation": "<p>üìù <u>T√≥m t·∫Øt ƒë·ªÅ:</u></p><ul><li><p>Developer storing <strong>many objects</strong> trong <strong>single S3 bucket</strong></p></li><li><p>C·∫ßn <strong>optimize S3 bucket for high request rates</strong></p></li><li><p>H·ªèi: c√°ch n√†o ƒë·ªÉ store objects ƒë√°p ·ª©ng y√™u c·∫ßu?</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚úÖ <u>ƒê√°p √°n ƒë√∫ng:</u></p><p><strong>Store the objects by using object key names distributed across multiple prefixes.</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Multiple prefixes</strong> ph√¢n t√°n requests across multiple partitions trong S3</p></li><li><p>S3 t·ª± ƒë·ªông scale performance theo s·ªë prefixes</p></li><li><p><strong>3,500 PUT/COPY/POST/DELETE</strong> v√† <strong>5,500 GET/HEAD requests per second per prefix</strong></p></li><li><p>Nhi·ªÅu prefixes = tƒÉng t·ªïng throughput</p></li></ul><p></p><p><u>C√°c ƒë√°p √°n sai:</u></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Store the objects by using S3 Intelligent-Tiering.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Intelligent-Tiering l√† <strong>storage class</strong> ƒë·ªÉ optimize costs, kh√¥ng ph·∫£i performance</p></li><li><p>Kh√¥ng ·∫£nh h∆∞·ªüng ƒë·∫øn request rates</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Store the objects at the root of the S3 bucket.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Root level (single prefix) b·ªã gi·ªõi h·∫°n performance</p></li><li><p>Kh√¥ng ph√¢n t√°n requests, kh√¥ng optimize cho high request rates</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Store each object with an object tag named \"prefix\" that contains a unique value.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Object tags d√πng cho organization v√† lifecycle policies, kh√¥ng ·∫£nh h∆∞·ªüng performance</p></li><li><p>Tags kh√¥ng ph√¢n t√°n requests</p></li></ul><p></p><p>üîë <u>Tips and tricks:</u></p><ul><li><p><strong>\"High request rates\" + \"S3 optimization\"</strong> ‚Üí <strong>Multiple prefixes</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>S3 performance limits</strong>: 3,500-5,500 requests/second <strong>per prefix</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Prefix examples</strong>: <code>/images/</code>, <code>/videos/</code>, <code>/2024/01/</code>, <code>/user-123/</code></p></li><li><p><strong>Intelligent-Tiering</strong> = cost optimization, kh√¥ng ph·∫£i performance</p></li></ul><p></p><p>üìñ <u>Reference:</u></p><ul><li><p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/userguide/optimizing-performance.html\">Best practices design patterns: optimizing Amazon S3 performance</a></p></li></ul>",
