            "questionText": "<p>A developer is working on an ecommerce platform that communicates with several third-party payment processing APIs. The third-party payment services do not provide a test environment.<br><br>The developer needs to validate the ecommerce platform's integration with the third-party payment processing APIs. The developer must test the API integration code without invoking the third-party payment processing APIs.<br><br>Which solution will meet these requirements?</p>",
            "explanation": "<p>üìù <u>T√≥m t·∫Øt ƒë·ªÅ:</u></p><ul><li><p>Developer l√†m <strong>ecommerce platform</strong> communicate v·ªõi <strong>several third-party payment processing APIs</strong></p></li><li><p>Third-party services <strong>kh√¥ng provide test environment</strong></p></li><li><p>C·∫ßn <strong>validate integration</strong> v·ªõi third-party APIs</p></li><li><p>Ph·∫£i <strong>test API integration code WITHOUT invoking</strong> third-party APIs</p></li><li><p>H·ªèi: solution n√†o ƒë√°p ·ª©ng y√™u c·∫ßu?</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚úÖ <u>ƒê√°p √°n ƒë√∫ng:</u></p><p><strong>Set up an Amazon API Gateway REST API for each third-party API. Specify an integration request type of Mock. Configure integration responses by using sample responses captured from the real third-party API.</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>API Gateway Mock integration</strong> tr·∫£ v·ªÅ responses ƒë·ªãnh s·∫µn m√† kh√¥ng g·ªçi backend</p></li><li><p><strong>Kh√¥ng invoke</strong> third-party APIs</p></li><li><p><strong>Configure responses</strong> v·ªõi sample data t·ª´ real API</p></li><li><p>Cho ph√©p test integration code v·ªõi responses th·ª±c t·∫ø</p></li></ul><p></p><p><u>C√°c ƒë√°p √°n sai:</u></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Set up an Amazon API Gateway REST API with a gateway response configured for status code 200. Add response templates that contain sample responses captured from the real third-party API.</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Gateway responses</strong> d√πng cho error handling (4xx, 5xx), kh√¥ng ph·∫£i mock normal API responses</p></li><li><p>Kh√¥ng ph√π h·ª£p cho testing integration code</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Set up an AWS AppSync GraphQL API with a data source configured for each third-party API. Specify an integration type of Mock. Configure integration responses by using sample responses captured from the real third-party API.</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>AppSync</strong> l√† GraphQL service, kh√¥ng ph√π h·ª£p cho REST-based payment APIs</p></li><li><p>Third-party payment APIs th∆∞·ªùng l√† REST, kh√¥ng ph·∫£i GraphQL</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Create an AWS Lambda function for each third-party API. Embed responses captured from the real third-party API. Configure Amazon Route 53 Resolver with an inbound endpoint for each Lambda function's Amazon Resource Name (ARN).</strong></p><ul><li><p>Qu√° ph·ª©c t·∫°p v·ªõi Lambda functions v√† Route 53</p></li><li><p>Route 53 Resolver kh√¥ng d√πng cho API mocking</p></li></ul><p></p><p>üîë <u>Tips and tricks:</u></p><ul><li><p><strong>\"Test without invoking external APIs\"</strong> ‚Üí <strong>API Gateway Mock integration</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Mock integration</strong> = return responses ƒë∆∞·ª£c x√°c ƒë·ªãnh tr∆∞·ªõc, kh√¥ng call backend</p></li><li><p><strong>Gateway responses</strong> = error handling, kh√¥ng ph·∫£i mocking</p></li><li><p><strong>AppSync</strong> = GraphQL, payment APIs th∆∞·ªùng l√† REST</p></li></ul><p></p><p>üìñ <u>Reference:</u></p><ul><li><p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/apigateway/latest/developerguide/how-to-mock-integration.html\">Mock integrations for REST APIs in API Gateway</a></p></li></ul>",
