            "questionId": 5358,
            "questionText": "<p>A company runs a payment application on Amazon EC2 instances behind an Application Load Balance. The EC2 instances run in an Auto Scaling group across multiple Availability Zones. The application needs to retrieve application secrets during the application startup and export the secrets as environment variables. These secrets must be encrypted at rest and need to be rotated every month.<br><br>Which solution will meet these requirements with the LEAST development effort?</p>",
            "explanation": "<p>üìù <u>T√≥m t·∫Øt ƒë·ªÅ:</u></p><ul><li><p>Payment application ch·∫°y tr√™n <strong>EC2 instances</strong> behind <strong>ALB</strong></p></li><li><p>EC2 trong <strong>Auto Scaling group</strong> across <strong>multiple AZs</strong></p></li><li><p>Application c·∫ßn <strong>retrieve secrets during startup</strong> v√† <strong>export as environment variables</strong></p></li><li><p>Secrets ph·∫£i <strong>encrypted at rest</strong> v√† <strong>rotated every month</strong></p></li><li><p>H·ªèi: solution v·ªõi <strong>LEAST development effort</strong>?</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚úÖ <u>ƒê√°p √°n ƒë√∫ng:</u></p><p><strong>Store the secrets in AWS Secrets Manager. Provision a new customer master key. Use the key to encrypt the secrets. Enable automatic rotation. Configure an Amazon EC2 user data script to programmatically retrieve the secrets during the startup and export as environment variables.</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Secrets Manager</strong> ƒë∆∞·ª£c thi·∫øt k·∫ø ƒë·∫∑c bi·ªát cho secrets management</p></li><li><p><strong>Automatic rotation</strong> built-in - ch·ªâ c·∫ßn enable, kh√¥ng c·∫ßn custom code</p></li><li><p><strong>Encrypted at rest</strong> by default v·ªõi KMS</p></li><li><p><strong>User data script</strong> retrieve secrets khi EC2 startup</p></li><li><p><strong>LEAST effort</strong> - Secrets Manager handle rotation automatically</p></li></ul><p></p><p><em>V√≠ d·ª•: User Data Script (Bash)</em></p><pre><code>#!/bin/bash\n\n# Install AWS CLI (n·∫øu ch∆∞a c√≥)\nyum install -y aws-cli\n\n# Retrieve secret t·ª´ Secrets Manager\nSECRET_JSON=$(aws secretsmanager get-secret-value \\\n    --secret-id prod/payment-app/credentials \\\n    --region us-east-1 \\\n    --query SecretString \\\n    --output text)\n\n# Parse JSON v√† export as environment variables\nexport DB_USERNAME=$(echo $SECRET_JSON | jq -r '.username')\nexport DB_PASSWORD=$(echo $SECRET_JSON | jq -r '.password')\nexport API_KEY=$(echo $SECRET_JSON | jq -r '.api_key')\n\n# Write v√†o /etc/environment ƒë·ªÉ persist\necho \"DB_USERNAME=$DB_USERNAME\" &gt;&gt; /etc/environment\necho \"DB_PASSWORD=$DB_PASSWORD\" &gt;&gt; /etc/environment\necho \"API_KEY=$API_KEY\" &gt;&gt; /etc/environment\n\n# Start application\ncd /opt/payment-app\n./start-app.sh</code></pre><p></p><p><u>C√°c ƒë√°p √°n sai:</u></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Save the secrets in a text file and store the text file in Amazon S3. Provision a customer managed key. Use the key for secret encryption in Amazon S3. Read the contents of the text file and read the export as environment variables. Configure S3 Object Lambda to rotate the text file every month.</strong></p><ul><li><p>S3 kh√¥ng ph·∫£i secrets management solution</p></li><li><p><strong>S3 Object Lambda</strong> kh√¥ng d√πng cho rotation, require custom implementation</p></li><li><p>High development effort</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Save the secrets as strings in AWS Systems Manager Parameter Store and use the default AWS Key Management Service (AWS KMS) key. Configure an Amazon EC2 user data script to retrieve the secrets during the startup and export as environment variables. Configure an AWS Lambda function to rotate the secrets in Parameter Store every month.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Parameter Store kh√¥ng c√≥ <strong>automatic rotation</strong> feature</p></li><li><p><strong>Require custom Lambda function</strong> ƒë·ªÉ rotate - more development effort</p></li><li><p>Secrets Manager t·ªët h∆°n cho secrets v·ªõi rotation requirements</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Save the secrets as base64 encoded environment variables in the application properties. Retrieve the secrets during the application startup. Reference the secrets in the application code. Write a script to rotate the secrets saved as environment variables.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Base64 encoding <strong>kh√¥ng ph·∫£i encryption</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Not encrypted at rest</strong></p></li><li><p>Require custom rotation script - high development effort</p></li></ul><p></p><p>üîë <u>Tips and tricks:</u></p><ul><li><p><strong>\"Secrets + automatic rotation\"</strong> ‚Üí <strong>AWS Secrets Manager</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Parameter Store vs Secrets Manager</strong>:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Parameter Store</strong> = no built-in rotation</p></li><li><p><strong>Secrets Manager</strong> = automatic rotation built-in</p></li></ul></li><li><p><strong>\"LEAST development effort\" + \"rotation\"</strong> ‚Üí Secrets Manager</p></li><li><p><strong>Base64 encoding ‚â† encryption</strong></p></li></ul><p></p><p>üìñ <u>Reference:</u></p><ul><li><p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/secretsmanager/latest/userguide/rotating-secrets.html\">Rotating AWS Secrets Manager secrets</a></p></li></ul><p>User data script ch·ªâ ch·∫°y 1 l·∫ßn khi FIRST LAUNCH, kh√¥ng ch·∫°y l·∫°i khi stop/start. V·∫≠y n·∫øu stop v√† start th√¨ l√†m sao ƒë·ªÉ l·∫•y ƒë∆∞·ª£c bi√™n m√¥i tr∆∞·ªùng.</p><ol><li><p>Application retrieve secrets at runtime (Best Practice)</p></li><li><p>Use systemd service to run script on every boot</p></li></ol>",
