            "questionText": "<p>A developer is building a microservices-based application by using Python on AWS and several AWS services. The developer must use AWS X-Ray. The developer views the service map by using the console to view the service dependencies. During testing, the developer notices that some services are missing from the service map.<br><br>What can the developer do to ensure that all services appear in the X-Ray service map?</p>",
            "explanation": "<p>üìù <u>T√≥m t·∫Øt ƒë·ªÅ:</u></p><ul><li><p>Developer build <strong>microservices application</strong> b·∫±ng <strong>Python</strong> tr√™n AWS</p></li><li><p>Ph·∫£i s·ª≠ d·ª•ng <strong>AWS X-Ray</strong></p></li><li><p>Developer view <strong>service map</strong> trong console ƒë·ªÉ xem <strong>service dependencies</strong></p></li><li><p>During testing: <strong>some services missing</strong> from service map</p></li><li><p>H·ªèi: l√†m g√¨ ƒë·ªÉ ensure <strong>all services appear (xu·∫•t hi·ªán)</strong> trong X-Ray service map?</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚úÖ <u>ƒê√°p √°n ƒë√∫ng:</u></p><p><strong>Instrument the application by using the X-Ray SDK for Python. Install the X-Ray SDK for all the services that the application uses.</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>X-Ray SDK</strong> instrument code ƒë·ªÉ send trace data ƒë·∫øn X-Ray</p></li><li><p><strong>Missing services</strong> = ch∆∞a ƒë∆∞·ª£c instrumented v·ªõi X-Ray SDK</p></li><li><p>Ph·∫£i install v√† configure X-Ray SDK trong <strong>t·∫•t c·∫£ services</strong> ƒë·ªÉ ch√∫ng xu·∫•t hi·ªán tr√™n service map</p></li><li><p>SDK capture requests, responses, v√† calls ƒë·∫øn downstream services</p></li></ul><p></p><p><u>C√°c ƒë√°p √°n sai:</u></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Modify the X-Ray Python agent configuration in each service to increase the sampling rate.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Sampling rate control <strong>bao nhi√™u % requests ƒë∆∞·ª£c traced</strong>, kh√¥ng ph·∫£i services n√†o ƒë∆∞·ª£c xu·∫•t hi·ªán</p></li><li><p>N·∫øu service ch∆∞a instrumented, tƒÉng sampling rate kh√¥ng gi√∫p service xu·∫•t hi·ªán</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Enable X-Ray data aggregation in Amazon CloudWatch Logs for all the services that the application uses.</strong></p><ul><li><p>X-Ray kh√¥ng require CloudWatch Logs aggregation ƒë·ªÉ show services tr√™n service map</p></li><li><p>Missing services do thi·∫øu instrumentation, kh√¥ng ph·∫£i logs configuration</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Increase the X-Ray service map timeout value in the X-Ray console.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Service map timeout kh√¥ng li√™n quan ƒë·∫øn missing services</p></li><li><p>Kh√¥ng c√≥ setting nh∆∞ v·∫≠y trong X-Ray console</p></li></ul><p></p><p>üîë <u>Tips and tricks:</u></p><ul><li><p><strong>\"Services missing from X-Ray service map\"</strong> ‚Üí <strong>Ch∆∞a instrumented v·ªõi X-Ray SDK</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>X-Ray SDK</strong> ph·∫£i ƒë∆∞·ª£c install v√† configured trong <strong>every service</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Sampling rate</strong> = % of requests traced, kh√¥ng ·∫£nh h∆∞·ªüng service visibility</p></li><li><p><strong>CloudWatch Logs</strong> kh√¥ng required cho X-Ray service map</p></li></ul><p></p><p>üìñ <u>Reference:</u></p><ul><li><p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/lambda/latest/dg/python-tracing.html\">Instrumenting Python code in AWS Lambda</a></p></li></ul>",
