            "questionId": 5361,
            "questionText": "<p>A developer is creating a simple proof-of-concept demo by using AWS CloudFormation and AWS Lambda functions. The demo will use a CloudFormation template to deploy an existing Lambda function. The Lambda function uses deployment packages and dependencies stored in Amazon S3. The developer defined an AWS::Lambda::Function resource in a CloudFormation template. The developer needs to add the S3 bucket to the CloudFormation template.<br><br>What should the developer do to meet these requirements with the LEAST development effort?</p>",
            "explanation": "<p>üìù <u>T√≥m t·∫Øt ƒë·ªÅ:</u></p><ul><li><p>Developer t·∫°o <strong>proof-of-concept demo</strong> b·∫±ng <strong>CloudFormation v√† Lambda</strong></p></li><li><p>Demo s·∫Ω d√πng CloudFormation template ƒë·ªÉ <strong>deploy existing Lambda function</strong></p></li><li><p>Lambda function d√πng <strong>deployment packages v√† dependencies stored trong S3</strong></p></li><li><p>Developer ƒë√£ define <strong>AWS::Lambda::Function resource</strong> trong CloudFormation template</p></li><li><p>C·∫ßn <strong>add S3 bucket</strong> v√†o CloudFormation template</p></li><li><p>H·ªèi: c√°ch n√†o v·ªõi <strong>LEAST development effort</strong>?</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚úÖ <u>ƒê√°p √°n ƒë√∫ng:</u></p><p><strong>Add the relevant key and bucket to the S3Bucket and S3Key properties in the CloudFormation template.</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>S3Bucket v√† S3Key properties</strong> reference existing deployment package trong S3</p></li><li><p><strong>LEAST effort</strong> - ch·ªâ c·∫ßn specify bucket name v√† object key</p></li><li><p>Kh√¥ng c·∫ßn copy/embed code v√†o template</p></li><li><p>Lambda function ƒë√£ c√≥ deployment package s·∫µn trong S3</p></li></ul><p></p><p><u>C√°c ƒë√°p √°n sai:</u></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Add the function code in the CloudFormation template inline as the code property.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Inline code ch·ªâ support cho <strong>simple functions</strong>, kh√¥ng support <strong>dependencies</strong></p></li><li><p>ƒê·ªÅ b√†i n√≥i function c√≥ dependencies stored in S3</p></li><li><p>High effort - ph·∫£i copy code v√†o template</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Add the function code in the CloudFormation template as the ZipFile property.</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>ZipFile</strong> d√πng cho inline code (simple functions without dependencies)</p></li><li><p>Kh√¥ng support external dependencies t·ª´ S3</p></li><li><p>Kh√¥ng ph√π h·ª£p v·ªõi existing deployment package</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Find the S3 key for the Lambda function. Add the S3 key as the ZipFile property in the CloudFormation template.</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>ZipFile property</strong> kh√¥ng accept S3 key</p></li><li><p>ZipFile ch·ªâ d√πng cho inline code string</p></li><li><p>Syntax sai</p></li></ul><p></p><p>üîë <u>Tips and tricks:</u></p><ul><li><p><strong>\"Lambda deployment package in S3\"</strong> ‚Üí <strong>S3Bucket v√† S3Key properties</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Code property types</strong>:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Inline/ZipFile</strong> = simple code without dependencies</p></li><li><p><strong>S3Bucket/S3Key</strong> = deployment package in S3 (with dependencies)</p></li></ul></li><li><p><strong>\"LEAST effort\" + \"existing package in S3\"</strong> ‚Üí reference S3 location</p></li><li><p><strong>ZipFile ‚â† S3 key</strong> - ZipFile l√† inline code</p></li></ul><p></p><p>üìñ <u>Reference:</u></p><ul><li><p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSCloudFormation/latest/TemplateReference/aws-properties-lambda-function-code.html\">AWS::Lambda::Function Code property</a></p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>V√≠ d·ª•:</strong></p><p>CloudFormation Template (YAML)</p><pre><code>AWSTemplateFormatVersion: '2010-09-09'\nDescription: Deploy Lambda function from S3\n\nResources:\n  MyLambdaExecutionRole:\n    Type: AWS::IAM::Role\n    Properties:\n      AssumeRolePolicyDocument:\n        Version: '2012-10-17'\n        Statement:\n          - Effect: Allow\n            Principal:\n              Service: lambda.amazonaws.com\n            Action: sts:AssumeRole\n      ManagedPolicyArns:\n        - arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/service-role/AWSLambdaBasicExecutionRole\n\n  MyLambdaFunction:\n    Type: AWS::Lambda::Function\n    Properties:\n      FunctionName: MyDemoFunction\n      Runtime: python3.11\n      Handler: lambda_function.lambda_handler\n      Role: !GetAtt MyLambdaExecutionRole.Arn\n      Code:\n        S3Bucket: my-lambda-deployments-bucket      # S3 Bucket name\n        S3Key: functions/my-function-v1.0.zip       # S3 Object key\n      Timeout: 30\n      MemorySize: 128\n\nOutputs:\n  LambdaFunctionArn:\n    Description: Lambda Function ARN\n    Value: !GetAtt MyLambdaFunction.Arn</code></pre><p></p><p>Structure c·ªßa S3 deployment package:</p><pre><code>my-lambda-deployments-bucket/\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ functions/\n    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ my-function-v1.0.zip\n        ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ lambda_function.py       # Main handler\n        ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ requirements.txt\n        ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ dependencies/            # External libraries\n            ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ requests/\n            ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ boto3/</code></pre><p></p><p><strong>Deployment Steps:</strong></p><ol><li><p>Upload deployment package l√™n S3:</p></li></ol><pre><code class=\"language-bash\">aws s3 cp my-function-v1.0.zip s3://my-lambda-deployments-bucket/functions/</code></pre><p></p><ol start=\"2\"><li><p>Deploy CloudFormation stack:</p></li></ol><pre><code class=\"language-bash\">aws cloudformation create-stack \\\n  --stack-name lambda-demo-stack \\\n  --template-body file://template.yaml \\\n  --capabilities CAPABILITY_IAM</code></pre><p></p><ol start=\"3\"><li><p><strong>Done!</strong> Lambda function deployed t·ª´ S3 package! </p></li></ol>",
