            "questionId": 5364,
            "questionText": "<p>A developer is creating a publicly accessible enterprise website consisting of only static assets. The developer is hosting the website in Amazon S3 and serving the website to users through an Amazon CloudFront distribution. The users of this application must not be able to access the application content directly from an S3 bucket. All content must be served through the Amazon CloudFront distribution.<br><br>Which solution will meet these requirements?</p>",
            "explanation": "<p>üìù <u>T√≥m t·∫Øt ƒë·ªÅ:</u></p><ul><li><p>Developer t·∫°o <strong>publicly accessible website</strong> v·ªõi <strong>only static assets</strong></p></li><li><p>Hosting website trong <strong>S3</strong> v√† serve qua <strong>CloudFront distribution</strong></p></li><li><p>Users <strong>must NOT</strong> access content tr·ª±c ti·∫øp t·ª´ <strong>S3 bucket</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>All content</strong> ph·∫£i served qua <strong>CloudFront distribution</strong></p></li><li><p>H·ªèi: solution n√†o ƒë√°p ·ª©ng y√™u c·∫ßu?</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚úÖ <u>ƒê√°p √°n ƒë√∫ng:</u></p><p><strong>Create a new origin access control (OAC) in CloudFront. Configure the CloudFront distribution's origin to use the new OAC. Update the S3 bucket policy to allow CloudFront OAC with read and write access to access Amazon S3 as the origin.</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>OAC (Origin Access Control)</strong> cho ph√©p CloudFront access S3 m√† kh√¥ng c·∫ßn public S3 bucket</p></li><li><p><strong>Block direct S3 access</strong> - users ch·ªâ c√≥ th·ªÉ access qua CloudFront</p></li><li><p><strong>S3 bucket policy</strong> grant permissions ch·ªâ cho CloudFront OAC</p></li><li><p><strong>Recommended approach</strong> - OAC l√† successor c·ªßa OAI (Origin Access Identity)</p></li></ul><p></p><p><em>V√≠ d·ª• bucket policy:</em></p><pre><code>{\n  \"Version\": \"2012-10-17\",\n  \"Statement\": [\n    {\n      \"Sid\": \"AllowCloudFrontOAC\",\n      \"Effect\": \"Allow\",\n      \"Principal\": {\n        \"Service\": \"cloudfront.amazonaws.com\"\n      },\n      \"Action\": \"s3:GetObject\",\n      \"Resource\": \"arn:aws:s3:::my-website-bucket/*\",\n      \"Condition\": {\n        \"StringEquals\": {\n          \"AWS:SourceArn\": \"arn:aws:cloudfront::123456789012:distribution/EDFDVBD6EXAMPLE\"\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}</code></pre><p></p><p><u>C√°c ƒë√°p √°n sai:</u></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Update the S3 bucket settings. Enable the block all public access setting in Amazon S3. Configure the CloudFront distribution's with Amazon S3 as the origin. Update the S3 bucket policy to allow CloudFront write access.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Block public access l√† ƒë√∫ng nh∆∞ng <strong>thi·∫øu OAC configuration</strong></p></li><li><p>Kh√¥ng specify c√°ch CloudFront authenticate v·ªõi S3</p></li><li><p>CloudFront kh√¥ng c·∫ßn <strong>write access</strong> cho static website (ch·ªâ c·∫ßn read)</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Update the S3 bucket's static website settings. Enable static website hosting and specifying index and error documents. Update the CloudFront origin to use the S3 bucket's website endpoint.</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>S3 website endpoint</strong> l√† <strong>public</strong>, kh√¥ng th·ªÉ restrict access</p></li><li><p>Users v·∫´n c√≥ th·ªÉ access tr·ª±c ti·∫øp qua S3 website URL</p></li><li><p>Kh√¥ng ƒë√°p ·ª©ng requirement \"prevent direct access\"</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Update the CloudFront distribution's origin to send a custom header. Update the S3 bucket policy with a condition by using the aws:RequestTag/tag-key key. Configure the tag-key as the custom header name, and the value being matched is the header's value.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Custom header approach <strong>kh√¥ng secure</strong> - users c√≥ th·ªÉ gi·∫£ m·∫°o headers</p></li><li><p><strong>aws:RequestTag</strong> kh√¥ng d√πng cho validate custom headers</p></li><li><p>Kh√¥ng ph·∫£i best practice</p></li></ul><p></p><p>üîë <u>Tips and tricks:</u></p><ul><li><p><strong>\"CloudFront + S3 + prevent direct access\"</strong> ‚Üí <strong>Origin Access Control (OAC)</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>OAC vs OAI</strong>:</p><ul><li><p><strong>OAC</strong> = newer, recommended (support SSE-KMS, dynamic requests)</p></li><li><p><strong>OAI</strong> = legacy (still works but OAC preferred)</p></li></ul></li><li><p><strong>S3 website endpoint</strong> = public, kh√¥ng restrict ƒë∆∞·ª£c access</p></li><li><p><strong>Custom headers</strong> kh√¥ng secure cho authentication</p></li></ul><p></p><p>üìñ <u>Reference:</u></p><ul><li><p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonCloudFront/latest/DeveloperGuide/private-content-restricting-access-to-s3.html\">Restrict access to an Amazon S3 origin</a></p></li></ul>",
