            "questionText": "<p>A developer is building an application that invokes AWS Lambda functions asynchronously to process events. The developer notices that a Lambda function fails to process some events at random times. The developer needs to investigate the failed events and capture the events that the Lambda function fails to process.<br><br>Which solution will meet these requirements?</p>",
            "explanation": "<p>üìù <u>T√≥m t·∫Øt ƒë·ªÅ:</u></p><ul><li><p>Developer build application invoke <strong>Lambda functions asynchronously</strong></p></li><li><p>Lambda function <strong>fails to process some events at random times</strong></p></li><li><p>Developer c·∫ßn <strong>investigate failed events</strong> v√† <strong>capture events m√† Lambda fails to process</strong></p></li><li><p>H·ªèi: solution n√†o ƒë√°p ·ª©ng y√™u c·∫ßu?</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚úÖ <u>ƒê√°p √°n ƒë√∫ng:</u></p><p><strong>Configure the Lambda function with an Amazon Simple Queue Service (Amazon SQS) dead-letter queue. Update the Lambda function's execution role with the required permissions.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Dead-letter queue (DLQ) capture failed events t·ª´ async Lambda invocations</p></li><li><p>SQS DLQ l∆∞u tr·ªØ events m√† Lambda fail to process sau retry attempts</p></li><li><p>Developer c√≥ th·ªÉ investigate failed events trong SQS queue</p></li><li><p>Lambda execution role c·∫ßn permissions ƒë·ªÉ send messages ƒë·∫øn SQS DLQ</p></li></ul><p></p><p><u>C√°c ƒë√°p √°n sai:</u></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Add an Amazon EventBridge rule for the Lambda function. Configure the EventBridge rule to react to failed events and to store the events in an Amazon DynamoDB table.</strong></p><ul><li><p>EventBridge kh√¥ng automatically capture Lambda failed events</p></li><li><p>C·∫ßn custom configuration v√† kh√¥ng ph·∫£i standard pattern cho DLQ</p></li><li><p>More complex setup</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Configure the Lambda function with a dead-letter queue based in Amazon Kinesis. Update the Lambda function's execution role with the required permissions.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Lambda async invocation DLQ kh√¥ng support Kinesis</p></li><li><p>Valid destinations: SQS, SNS, S3, Lambda, EventBridge only</p></li><li><p>Kinesis kh√¥ng ph·∫£i valid DLQ destination</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Configure the Lambda function with an Amazon Simple Queue Service (Amazon SQS) FIFO dead-letter queue. Update the Lambda function's execution role with the required permissions.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Lambda DLQ ch·ªâ support <strong>SQS standard queue</strong>, kh√¥ng support FIFO</p></li><li><p>FIFO queue kh√¥ng ph·∫£i valid destination cho Lambda DLQ</p></li></ul><p></p><p>üîë <u>Tips and tricks:</u></p><ul><li><p>\"Async Lambda\" + \"capture failed events\" ‚Üí <strong>Dead-letter queue (DLQ)</strong></p></li><li><p>Lambda async DLQ destinations: SQS (standard only), SNS, S3, Lambda, EventBridge</p></li><li><p>SQS FIFO kh√¥ng support cho Lambda DLQ</p></li><li><p>Kinesis kh√¥ng ph·∫£i valid DLQ destination</p></li><li><p>SQS standard queue = simplest v√† most common cho DLQ</p></li></ul><p></p><p>üìñ <u>Reference:</u></p><ul><li><p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/lambda/latest/dg/invocation-async-retain-records.html\">Capturing records of Lambda asynchronous invocations</a></p></li></ul>",
