            "attemptAnswerId": 329588,
            "questionId": 5378,
            "questionText": "<p>A developer uses AWS CloudFormation to deploy an Amazon API Gateway API and an AWS Step Functions state machine. The state machine must reference the API Gateway API after the CloudFormation template is deployed. The developer needs a solution that uses the state machine to reference the API Gateway endpoint.<br><br>Which solution will meet these requirements MOST cost-effectively?</p>",
            "explanation": "<p>üìù <u>T√≥m t·∫Øt ƒë·ªÅ:</u></p><ul><li><p>Developer d√πng <strong>CloudFormation deploy API Gateway v√† Step Functions state machine</strong></p></li><li><p>State machine ph·∫£i <strong>reference API Gateway API endpoint</strong> sau khi template deployed</p></li><li><p>H·ªèi: solution n√†o <strong>MOST cost-effectively</strong>?</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚úÖ <u>ƒê√°p √°n ƒë√∫ng:</u></p><p><strong>Configure the CloudFormation template to reference the API endpoint in the DefinitionSubstitutions property for the AWS::StepFunctions::StateMachine resource.</strong></p><ul><li><p>DefinitionSubstitutions cho ph√©p pass dynamic values v√†o state machine definition khi deploy</p></li><li><p>CloudFormation automatically substitute API endpoint v√†o state machine</p></li><li><p>MOST cost-effective - zero cost, built-in CloudFormation feature</p></li></ul><p></p><p><u>C√°c ƒë√°p √°n sai:</u></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Configure the CloudFormation template to store the API endpoint in an environment variable for the AWS::StepFunctions::StateMachine resource. Configure the state machine to reference the environment variable.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Step Functions state machines kh√¥ng support environment variables</p></li><li><p>Environment variables ch·ªâ available cho Lambda functions</p></li><li><p>Kh√¥ng ph·∫£i valid solution</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Configure the CloudFormation template to store the API endpoint in a standard AWS::SecretsManager::Secret resource. Configure the state machine to reference the resource.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Secrets Manager c√≥ monthly cost per secret</p></li><li><p>Overkill cho public API endpoint (kh√¥ng ph·∫£i sensitive data)</p></li><li><p>Kh√¥ng cost-effective</p></li></ul><p></p><p>‚ùå <strong>Configure the CloudFormation template to store the API endpoint in a standard AWS::AppConfig::ConfigurationProfile resource. Configure the state machine to reference the resource.</strong></p><ul><li><p>AppConfig th√™m complexity v√† potential cost</p></li><li><p>Kh√¥ng c·∫ßn thi·∫øt cho static endpoint reference</p></li><li><p>DefinitionSubstitutions ƒë∆°n gi·∫£n h∆°n v√† free</p></li></ul><p></p><p>üîë <u>Tips and tricks:</u></p><ul><li><p>\"Step Functions reference values\" + \"CloudFormation\" ‚Üí <strong>DefinitionSubstitutions</strong></p></li><li><p>DefinitionSubstitutions = inject dynamic values v√†o state machine definition</p></li><li><p>Step Functions kh√¥ng c√≥ environment variables (kh√°c v·ªõi Lambda)</p></li></ul><p></p><p>üìñ <u>Reference:</u></p><ul><li><p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/serverless-application-model/latest/developerguide/sam-resource-statemachine.html\">AWS::StepFunctions::StateMachine DefinitionSubstitutions</a></p></li></ul><p><em>Code m·∫´u cho c√¢u ƒë√∫ng</em></p><pre><code>AWSTemplateFormatVersion: '2010-09-09'\nDescription: API Gateway and Step Functions with DefinitionSubstitutions\n\nResources:\n  MyApi:\n    Type: AWS::ApiGateway::RestApi\n    Properties:\n      Name: MyAPI\n\n  MyApiResource:\n    Type: AWS::ApiGateway::Resource\n    Properties:\n      ParentId: !GetAtt MyApi.RootResourceId\n      PathPart: items\n      RestApiId: !Ref MyApi\n\n  MyApiMethod:\n    Type: AWS::ApiGateway::Method\n    Properties:\n      AuthorizationType: NONE\n      HttpMethod: GET\n      ResourceId: !Ref MyApiResource\n      RestApiId: !Ref MyApi\n      Integration:\n        Type: MOCK\n        IntegrationResponses:\n          - StatusCode: 200\n        RequestTemplates:\n          application/json: '{\"statusCode\": 200}'\n      MethodResponses:\n        - StatusCode: 200\n\n  MyApiDeployment:\n    Type: AWS::ApiGateway::Deployment\n    DependsOn: MyApiMethod\n    Properties:\n      RestApiId: !Ref MyApi\n      StageName: prod\n\n  MyStateMachine:\n    Type: AWS::StepFunctions::StateMachine\n    Properties:\n      StateMachineName: MyStateMachine\n      RoleArn: !GetAtt StepFunctionsRole.Arn\n      DefinitionSubstitutions:\n        ApiEndpoint: !Sub \"https://${MyApi}.execute-api.${AWS::Region}.amazonaws.com/prod/items\"\n      DefinitionString: |\n        {\n          \"Comment\": \"Example using DefinitionSubstitutions\",\n          \"StartAt\": \"ProcessData\",\n          \"States\": {\n            \"ProcessData\": {\n              \"Type\": \"Pass\",\n              \"Result\": {\n                \"ApiEndpoint\": \"${ApiEndpoint}\"\n              },\n              \"End\": true\n            }\n          }\n        }\n\n  StepFunctionsRole:\n    Type: AWS::IAM::Role\n    Properties:\n      AssumeRolePolicyDocument:\n        Version: '2012-10-17'\n        Statement:\n          - Effect: Allow\n            Principal:\n              Service: states.amazonaws.com\n            Action: sts:AssumeRole\n\nOutputs:\n  ApiEndpoint:\n    Value: !Sub \"https://${MyApi}.execute-api.${AWS::Region}.amazonaws.com/prod/items\"\n  StateMachineArn:\n    Value: !Ref MyStateMachine</code></pre>",
